      "blocks": {
        "p_1": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Founded by Haruo Ito in 1938, ITO Bindery traded as a simple bookbinding business named Hakucho-do. When the business passed to Ito’s son, Toshio, in the late 1980s, the business changed a little too, adopting its current name.</p>"
          }
        },
        "p_2": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>It wasn’t until 2009 that ITO Bindery began developing the notepads that we know and love today, but they were almost immediate successes. Their sobriety belies a deft originality, the kind that comes from following an idea from beginning to end with thought and method.</p>"
          }
        },
